habitat_description:
Southwest:
Endemic to six of the eight Channel Islands off the California coast, this native species is common on Santa Cruz, Santa Rosa, and San Clemente islands, and less common on San Nicolas, San Miquel and Santa Catalina. They inhabitat mixed chapparal, coastal scrub, and valley foothill woodland shurb, denning among hollow stumps, dense brush, and rocky areas (Von Bloeker 1967,
Laughrin 1973, 1980, Philbrick 1967, Power 1980).
